I find it too on the nose.

511
00:26:44.792 --> 00:26:46.425
Oh, hey, look, look,
look, look! A second Chance!


512
00:26:46.428 --> 00:26:47.928
A guitar!

513
00:26:47.930 --> 00:26:50.163
- Hey, Merry Christmas, sweetie!
- Hey!


514
00:26:52.001 --> 00:26:53.967
I just got it as I said it.

515
00:26:53.969 --> 00:26:56.136
There goes a second Chance,

516
00:26:56.138 --> 00:26:58.272
'cause your...
your name is Chance, and...


517
00:26:58.274 --> 00:27:00.274
And, yeah,
yes, it was corny, okay,


518
00:27:00.276 --> 00:27:02.342
but, my God,
how could I not have said that?


519
00:27:06.048 --> 00:27:09.483
Oh! It's just the one I wanted!

520
00:27:10.452 --> 00:27:12.419
Oh, it must be
from Grandpa Jack.


521
00:27:12.421 --> 00:27:15.055
Grandpa, he's amazing.

522
00:27:15.057 --> 00:27:17.124
We told him you'd been
taking lessons, sweetie.


523
00:27:19.461 --> 00:27:21.461
Ah, Grandpa Jack.

524
00:27:21.463 --> 00:27:23.096
Couldn't make Christmas
once again,


525
00:27:23.098 --> 00:27:25.232
but look at those
nice presents he sent.


526
00:27:25.234 --> 00:27:28.936
I would have loved him,
no matter what.


527
00:27:28.938 --> 00:27:30.604
Mm-mm-mm. Let's put away

528
00:27:30.605 --> 00:27:32.271
that social media following
of yours for now, okay?


529
00:27:32.274 --> 00:27:34.041
This is about you, Cherry Bear.

530
00:27:34.043 --> 00:27:35.275
Don't call me that.

531
00:27:37.313 --> 00:27:40.180
Oh, that guitar,
that gift of love.


532
00:27:40.182 --> 00:27:42.616
It sure pushed you to practice,
huh? Am I wrong about that?


533
00:27:43.519 --> 00:27:45.319
Why are we here?

534
00:27:45.321 --> 00:27:48.021
Well, you know,
being a spirit has some perks.


535
00:27:48.023 --> 00:27:50.090
One, I get to help you
find your way.


536
00:27:50.092 --> 00:27:53.026
And, I consider
the most important,


537
00:27:53.028 --> 00:27:54.494
the drinks are free!

538
00:27:55.998 --> 00:27:58.131
That thing is
gonna make me so rich.


539
00:27:58.133 --> 00:27:59.399
Okay, I have
a notion that you're


540
00:27:59.401 --> 00:28:02.102
not exactly getting
the point of this,


541
00:28:02.104 --> 00:28:03.503
so we might need
to do this again.


542
00:28:03.505 --> 00:28:05.539
You know what?
Let's see it one more time.


543
00:28:10.546 --> 00:28:12.412
Chance: Whoa, whoa, whoa!

544
00:28:12.414 --> 00:28:15.382
Are we both watching the same
ghostly flashback thing?


545
00:28:15.384 --> 00:28:19.152
Because what I see
is a star in the making.


546
00:28:20.456 --> 00:28:23.223
Kiddo, we have
got some work to do.


547
00:28:28.397 --> 00:28:30.030
Oh, I remember this.

548
00:28:30.032 --> 00:28:32.232
This is the day. This is...

549
00:28:32.234 --> 00:28:34.468
This is "A.G.T.S.,"
the show that made me famous.


550
00:28:34.470 --> 00:28:36.136
Bingo! You hit that one

551
00:28:36.138 --> 00:28:37.471
straight out of the ballpark,
sweetheart.


552
00:28:37.473 --> 00:28:38.672
But now tell me this.

553
00:28:39.575 --> 00:28:41.608
Do you remember everything?

554
00:28:41.610 --> 00:28:44.077
But, Mom,
what if I forget the words?


555
00:28:44.079 --> 00:28:45.512
What if I don't want
to do it anymore?


556
00:28:45.514 --> 00:28:47.381
Is it too late
to tell them not to?


557
00:28:47.383 --> 00:28:49.182
You could do
whatever you want to do.


558
00:28:49.184 --> 00:28:51.284
I don't think
you want to quit. Do you?


559
00:28:51.286 --> 00:28:53.553
Plus, you're gonna
totally kill it.


560
00:28:53.555 --> 00:28:55.155
Thanks, Mom.

561
00:28:55.157 --> 00:28:57.124
All right.
I'm gonna get us some water.


562
00:28:57.126 --> 00:28:58.342
Okay.

563
00:28:59.561 --> 00:29:02.295
Don't worry, kid. You nail it.

564
00:29:05.034 --> 00:29:07.067
Without people like us,

565
00:29:07.069 --> 00:29:10.070
some people don't get to eat
or... or pay the bills.


566
00:29:10.072 --> 00:29:12.539
Like, they depend on us
for survival.


567
00:29:12.541 --> 00:29:14.574
People like us?

568
00:29:14.576 --> 00:29:18.178
Yeah, you know, stars.

569
00:29:18.180 --> 00:29:21.114
I don't think so.

570
00:29:22.151 --> 00:29:24.117
Well, you look
like a star to me.


571
00:29:25.120 --> 00:29:26.720
That's really sweet.

572
00:29:28.090 --> 00:29:30.357
Let me give you
a piece of advice.


573
00:29:30.359 --> 00:29:32.359
Always look out for number one.

574
00:29:32.361 --> 00:29:34.694
Give them your talent.
That's what the people want.


575
00:29:38.434 --> 00:29:39.550
Keep the rest for yourself.

576
00:29:39.551 --> 00:29:40.667
Do you really think
I could be a star?


577
00:29:43.539 --> 00:29:45.405
Oh, hello.

578
00:29:45.407 --> 00:29:47.207
Who's your new friend?

579
00:29:47.209 --> 00:29:50.477
Mom! It's Jason Cleavers.

580
00:29:50.479 --> 00:29:52.245
Are you one
of the contestants, too?


581
00:29:52.247 --> 00:29:54.481
That's cute.

582
00:29:54.483 --> 00:29:56.316
I'm the host.

583
00:30:01.356 --> 00:30:03.223
I didn't know.

584
00:30:03.225 --> 00:30:05.092
And what am I
supposed to learn


585
00:30:05.094 --> 00:30:06.493
about my mom embarrassing me?

586
00:30:06.495 --> 00:30:08.395
It wasn't about...

587
00:30:08.397 --> 00:30:11.364
It was about Jason
giving you bad advice.


588
00:30:11.366 --> 00:30:14.101
You know what?
Let's look a little forward.


589
00:30:14.103 --> 00:30:15.135
How 'bout a year?

590
00:30:21.276 --> 00:30:23.610
Is that Brian?

591
00:30:23.612 --> 00:30:25.612
I haven't thought
about this in years.


592
00:30:25.614 --> 00:30:29.249
Mm, he's thought
about it a lot.


593
00:30:32.588 --> 00:30:34.187
Yeah?

594
00:30:34.189 --> 00:30:36.657
Uh, hi, Mr. Love.

595
00:30:36.658 --> 00:30:39.126
I'm here to pick up Chance
for the Christmas Eve dance.


596
00:30:39.128 --> 00:30:41.495
Brian. Looking sharp, buddy.

597
00:30:42.598 --> 00:30:43.597
Hmm.

598
00:30:43.599 --> 00:30:44.598
Cherry Bea...Oh.

599
00:30:44.600 --> 00:30:45.765
I'm here.

600
00:30:47.503 --> 00:30:48.602
Wow.

601
00:30:48.604 --> 00:30:49.769
Hi.

602
00:30:50.672 --> 00:30:52.339
You look beautiful.

603
00:30:53.275 --> 00:30:55.208
Thank you. So do you.

604
00:30:55.210 --> 00:30:57.544
Hey, let me get a picture.
Mom will kill me if I don't.


605
00:30:57.546 --> 00:30:58.645
- Okay.
- All right.


606
00:30:58.647 --> 00:31:00.180
Get together now.

607
00:31:00.182 --> 00:31:02.716
All right, ready?

608
00:31:05.220 --> 00:31:06.687
Oh, yeah, that's awesome.

609
00:31:06.688 --> 00:31:08.155
All right, listen.

610
00:31:08.157 --> 00:31:10.290
Have fun. Drive safe, okay?

611
00:31:10.292 --> 00:31:11.558
- You got it, sir.
- Dad.


612
00:31:11.560 --> 00:31:13.593
11:00. 11:00.

613
00:31:13.595 --> 00:31:16.429
Agh, that dress!
What was I thinking?


614
00:31:16.431 --> 00:31:19.332
No, no. Shh, shh, shh.
This is the cute part.


615
00:31:21.503 --> 00:31:22.702
- Right here.
- Oh, right there.


616
00:31:22.704 --> 00:31:23.737
- Yeah!
- Okay.


617
00:31:23.739 --> 00:31:25.705
- Oh, my God.
- Gotcha.


618
00:31:27.543 --> 00:31:28.675
Chance: Thank you.

619
00:31:34.616 --> 00:31:36.550
Oh, boy.

620
00:31:36.552 --> 00:31:38.518
And now the sad part.

621
00:31:41.190 --> 00:31:42.789
Jason?

622
00:31:42.791 --> 00:31:44.591
What are you doing here?

623
00:31:44.593 --> 00:31:47.194
I got a show tonight,
lost my opener.


624
00:31:47.196 --> 00:31:48.595
How'd you like
to open for me?


625
00:31:48.597 --> 00:31:49.729
Are you serious?

626
00:31:49.731 --> 00:31:51.698
You wanna be a star?

627
00:31:57.673 --> 00:31:58.838
Chance.

628
00:32:12.621 --> 00:32:14.521
I'd like to go home now.

629
00:32:14.523 --> 00:32:16.489
Even after
you broke his heart,


630
00:32:16.491 --> 00:32:18.692
he followed you around
like a puppy dog.


631
00:32:18.694 --> 00:32:22.829
Now he does your bidding
without ever a word of thanks.


632
00:32:28.770 --> 00:32:31.304
I never meant to hurt him.

633
00:32:34.643 --> 00:32:37.711
He's the best friend
I've ever had.


634
00:32:37.713 --> 00:32:39.546
Do you ever tell him that?

635
00:32:44.253 --> 00:32:46.319
I said
I'd like to go home now.


636
00:32:46.321 --> 00:32:47.320
Mm-hmm.

637
00:32:47.322 --> 00:32:50.323
I said now!

638
00:32:58.400 --> 00:33:01.668
...designed to keep
the people in check.


639
00:33:01.670 --> 00:33:04.371
And so we celebrate.

